'''Dostonbek Khamdamov''' ({{lang-x2|uz|Dostonbek Xurshid oʻgʻli Xamdamov|Достонбек Хуршид ўғли Хамдамов}}; born 24 July 1996) is an Uzbek professional [[Association football|footballer]], [[Asian Young Footballer of the Year]]2015,<ref>{{Cite web |last=UzDaily |title=Dostonbek Khamdamov named AFC Youth player of the Year 2015 |url=https://www.uzdaily.uz/en/post/34424 |access-date=2023-06-24 |website=UzDaily.uz |language=ru}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Khamdomov receives AFC Youth Player of the Year Award |url=https://www.the-afc.com/en/more/news/khamdomov_receives_afc_youth_player_of_the_year_award.html |access-date=2023-06-24 |website=the-AFC |language=en}}</ref> winner of the [[2018 AFC U-23 Championship|Asian Youth Championship 2018]]<ref>{{Cite web |last=uza.uz |date=1970-01-01 |title=Uzbekistan National U23 Football Team became the champion of Asia |url=https://uza.uz/en/posts/uzbekistan-national-u23-football-team-became-the-champion-of-27-01-2018 |access-date=2023-06-24 |website=Uza.uz |language=uz}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=UzDaily |title=Uzbekistan wins AFC U23 Championship China 2018 title |url=http://www.uzdaily.com/en/post/42513 |access-date=2023-06-24 |website=UzDaily.uz |language=ru}}</ref> and plays as a [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]] for [[Pakhtakor Tashkent FK|Pakhtakor]]<ref>{{Cite web |title="ПАХТАКОР" Футбол клуби |url=http://www.pakhtakor.uz/team/players/179 |access-date=2023-06-24 |website=www.pakhtakor.uz}}</ref> and the [[Uzbekistan national football team|Uzbekistan national team]].

==Club career==
On 15 March 2018, Khamdamov was registered by [[Russian Premier League]] club [[FC Anzhi Makhachkala|Anzhi Makhachkala]], taking the #7 jersey after signing an 18-month contract.<ref name="RFPLregistration" /><ref>{{cite web|title=Достонбек Хамдамов - в Анжи|url=http://www.fc-anji.ru/news/ru/club_news/dostonbek_hamdamov_v_anji160318/|website=fc-anji.ru|publisher=FC Anzhi Makhachkala|access-date=16 March 2018|language=ru|date=16 March 2018|archive-date=26 June 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180626220456/http://www.fc-anji.ru/news/ru/club_news/dostonbek_hamdamov_v_anji160318/|url-status=dead}}</ref>
On 15 February 2019, Anzhi Makhachkala announced that Khamdamov had left the club to join [[Pakhtakor Tashkent FK|Pakhtakor Tashkent]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Хамдамов покинул Анжи |url=http://www.fc-anji.ru/news/ru/club_news/hamdamov_pokinul_anji150219/ |website=fc-anji.ru |publisher=FC Anzhi Makhachkala |access-date=15 February 2019 |language=ru |date=15 February 2019 |archive-date=8 December 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211208114529/http://fc-anji.ru/news/ru/club_news/hamdamov_pokinul_anji150219/ |url-status=dead }}</ref>

Khamdamov was released by Pakhtakor Tashkent on 13 January 2021.<ref>{{cite web |title=ЖЕЛАЕМ УДАЧИ ДОСТОНБЕКУ ХАМДАМОВУ |url=http://www.pakhtakor.uz/news/cnews/5192 |website=pakhtakor.uz/ |publisher=Pakhtakor Tashkent FK |access-date=12 March 2021 |language=Russian |date=13 January 2021}}</ref> On 23 July 2021, Khamdamov returned to Pakhtakor Tashkent, signing a contract until the end of 2022.<ref>{{cite web |title=ДОСТОНБЕК ҲАМДАМОВ ЯНА "ПАХТАКОР" ФУТБОЛЧИСИГА АЙЛАНДИ |url=http://www.pakhtakor.uz/news/cnews/5652 |website=pakhtakor.uz/ |publisher=Pakhtakor Tashkent FK |access-date=23 July 2021 |language=Uzbek |date=23 July 2021}}</ref> On 22 January 2022, Pakhtakor announced that Khamdamov had signed for [[Al-Sailiya SC|Al-Sailiya]] on loan until 30 June 2022.<ref>{{cite web |title=ДОСТОНБЕК ҲАМДАМОВ "АЛ САЙЛИЯ"ГА ИЖАРАГА БЕРИЛДИ |url=http://pakhtakor.uz/news/cnews/6021 |website=pakhtakor.uz/ |publisher=Pakhtakor Tashkent |access-date=24 January 2022 |language=Uzbek |date=22 January 2022}}</ref>

==International career==
[[File:TUR-UZB 20190113 Asian Cup 9.jpg|thumb|Khamdamov (№17) at 2019 Asian Cup]]
Khamdamov was part of the [[Uzbekistan national under-20 football team|U-19]] squad when they finished in the semi-finals of the [[2014 AFC U-19 Championship]], where Khamdamov scored one goal only. After that match, Khamdamov would go on to make an outstanding performance in the [[2015 FIFA U-20 World Cup]], where he scored three goals and produced a magnificent performance as Uzbekistan ran into the quarter-finals before bowing to Senegal. For this performance, he became the first Uzbek player to be nominated as the Asian Young Footballer of the Year.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20201103110808/https://www.fifa.com/u20worldcup/news/khamdamov-uzbekistan-are-out-to-make-history-2646227 FIFA.com]</ref><ref>{{cite web| url = https://www.the-afc.com/news/afcsection/afc-youth-player-of-the-year-men-2015-dostonbek-khamdamov-28230| title = the-afc.com}}</ref>

He participated in the [[2016 AFC U-23 Championship]] and scored two goals, but his team went out from the group stage. [[2018 AFC U-23 Championship|Two years later]], he would lead Uzbekistan to conquer the country's first-ever U-23 trophy. For this successful display, Khamdamov earned a place and would go to be part of the [[Uzbekistan national football team|senior squad]] for the [[2019 AFC Asian Cup]].

